<h6>Simple website that replaces the Excel sheet used by UT Epic for church rides. Not affiliated with official Epic Movement.</h6>
<h6>This is just a test demo. Only the basic aspects of the website have been implemented.</h6>
<h6>The data is stored remotely on an AWS server. No data is saved or distributed.</h6>
<h4>The church names have not been added, so it's just dummy names for now</h4>
<h2>Pages and What they Do</h2>
<p>This is the home page. The view page shows all the current rides. The edit page allows an individual to remove their sign up. The driver page is a WIP; it currently links to the error page, but it is supposed to include details for the drivers about their riders. The sign up pages are used to sign up as either riders or drivers</p>
<h2>Further Improvements</h2>
<p>BIG IMPLEMENTATION: Prevent signups past a certain timestamp and reset database every week</p>
<p>Plans to add validation for both phone numbers and emails</p>
<p>Plans to add Google Maps API to allow drivers to map the shortest distance from their location to all the riders and finally to the church.</p>
<p>Plans to add text messaging API that automatically pushes emails and text messages when people sign up for rides</p>
<p>Quality of life updates include dark mode, better readability for mobile, and filters/searches</p>
